caption: Really nice staff, great cocktails, and one of the better vibes in a Brooklyn bar. Owner is really cool, usually has his adorable and friendly service dog with him which is a bonus!
Super intimate open mic on monday and Tuesday!  Love the vibes. Met some really cool😎 people to add!
Great happy hour deals. $6 old fashion was excellent
My favorite local cocktail spot. Never too crowded. Great happy hour prices! And the cocktails are amazing.
A good watering hole to catch up with friends and have some tasty cocktails. Solid ambiance with enough space to be roomy
Excellent drinks poor hospitality.
Great drinks at reasonable prices. Comedy and other variety

Décor is nice and the wine was good, as were the fries. It's a shame though that there was no draught beer; and the food menu was bare-bones.  They only accepted cash, purportedly because the machine was broken. I normally avoid such places, so hopefully this does end up being fixed.
Fun cocktail bar with a back room for dancing and ample seating plus a backyard for a smoke & outdoor hang. Just near the Montrose stop.
Decent cocktails, but worst service.

It's fine.  Limited drinks limited food,  it's a great atmosphere but doesn't offer much more than that.  It'd be great if it had more than 2 beers on tap,  and the food menu is a little weak...... take it back,  the grilled cheese is awesome!!!!
The best local
RUDE
Great cocktails!
Great cocktail bar. Amazing staff. Huge space with an casual atmosphere

Very bad attitude from the bar tender or owner who was very rude and annoying  last night  , after two rounds to ask a glass of water was too much for him :  he refuses !  I will avoid this place , terrible experience ! I don't recommend at all ! there are much better place where they will treat you well and not only take your money
It's a cross between a dive bar and a she she tavern. The broken windows as you enter are a bummer.

Great spot. Owners are very thoughtful and professional. They have open mic nights which is so fun to meet new creative people. The bar eats are good too, like the grilled cheese and fries which are as good as the reviews say. I would recommend this spot to anyone in the area. C
Great open mic nights
The Destination Fries were on point. The grilled cheese also great tasting.  I tasted the Margaritas and rum and coke and they were delicious.

The place is gorgeous. The mirrors are amazing and the ambiance is just so cool. It doesn’t get too crowded so it’s a good place to meet friends and talk and drink together. The drinks are pretty good too and reasonably priced. The staff is very nice.

I think the drinks were decent and a little pricey for the area.  There wasn't food to eat if you're looking for dinner and drinks. It was more like small bites and finger food. The fries were good though.  Services was subpar, 3 bartenders, no servers on a not so busy night and I still had to approach the bar for service.  I wonder how the customers all the way in the back get a drink.

Romantic and cute. Really good fries and grilled cheese. The bartender was weird and literally checked his phone while taking my friend's order and then said "what" after she ordered but other than that, loved it.
One of the greatest bar to hang out with friends! Great cocktails! Great staff! Highly recommend it.
Great drinks, and the food was awesome! The staff friendly and all over a good romantic vibe.
Vibey cocktail bar great for a date night or cozy happy hour. One of my favorite neighborhood spots!
Great little spot with an extensive and creative cocktail list. Attentive bartenders
Awesome! Great bartenders! Ambiance is set beautifully at night
Nice drinks! And they have a dog. That's a win in my book.
Lovely space and a lovely group of people running things. Great cocktails in a very warm and inviting setting.
Great ambience and service.
Nice bar, was there on a Sunday night, was quiet. They make a Old Fashion. It had a back room with couches. Perfect place for dates.
I enjoyed
Cute bar with great open mic
Good neighborhood atmosphere. Managed to balance the cool vibe of a cocktail bar without any standoffish aloofness. Each area comfortable.
Great happy hour drinks and show
Small friendly bar with a nice room for music in the rear.

Chill spot with a low-key after work vibe - even on a Friday. Drinks are an 8/10, with prices really being out of control for a measured out drink. Try the Dead Man's Mask for their specialty drink - fruity with a bit of whiskey flair.

Drinks are extremely interesting, atmosphere very comfortable with an art deco feeling, and staff are amazingly reactive (in a positive way). I have had a great time, every time I have gone here and it wasn't because I was drunk af.
Very nice venue, great back yard, the cocktails are nice nothing crazy, the staff was amazing but it went down a little that’s wat it’s not 4 Stars to bad
Cool retro cozy atmosphere, great tunes, amazing cocktails.

Awesome spot. Love the classy retro ambience. Wish they had a slightly better happy hour, but prices are pretty good anyway.  They take cash and credit, unlike Post No Bills next door which is cash only.

Unique atmosphere  I attend this bar often and I really like it. As you enter they have a few tables and a nice bar, at the back they always have private invents and to my best knowledge , there is a terrace. At any point, if you feel bored, they have a chess set. From the menu, I would recommend pastrami salmon.
Super chill, low key bar with lots of space
Fantastic service—I tried the tequila old fashioned and a dirty martini and both were impeccable. The bartenders really know their stuff and are such a pleasure to talk to.
Amazing local spot. Great drinks and food all reasonably priced. Good for those looking for small plate meals. Excellent service. Friendly bartenders as well!
Good amount of space. Decent drink prices. Good food.
Staff was friendly and the food was good.
Fun place with good tapas.

Delicious cocktails and tasty food! The private room in the back can be reserved for parties and it has a separate sound system from the main room allowing you to have a dance party to whatever music you want with your friends!
Peppermint oil and rockchain. I'm bummed though. We're not going to house of yes.
Cool spot but drinks are pricey and the bartender always has an attitude
Dope bar!
Cozy and comfy drinks are reasonably priced. The staffing was very friendly.

This place is a cool spot; with a nice ambiance, staff, and its very low key. Wasn't crowded the night visited (possibly because of the bitter cold) but either way the drinks are reasonably priced and you can't ask for more from a Bushwick lounge.
Good spot. Don't come so it stays the way it is without you there
Great drinks and atmosphere. A smidge pricey for the area.

Food was good. Drinks could be better but the owner!!! That’s a different story, his attitude was disgusting and he was very inconsistent with his story to me. He has a “service dog” with no service tags. My guest were annoyed and unaware that we would be joined by a dog. And though we have no issues with service animals it would have been nice to know that frequent patrons bring animals and the Owner has a dog that would be in the place. If that would have been discussed prior too we could’ve had a very different choice in picking that venue for our event. He also put out 6 bottles of wine and 40 beers for $500- NO FOOD!! #RIPOFF

I wasn't crazy about the cocktail I got, but I did order french fries and they were so good I almost died. I love the aesthetic of this place & it helps that there's a very sweet dog that lives inside

Go there for cocktails! They had a diverse selection and the two I tried were very good. I went on a Thursday night and the place was alive but not too crowded. Laid back. Typical "Brooklyn hipster" with no outdoor signage.  Beer and wine were standard.  The food in the pic were potato fries which were cooked to perfection. Nice crisp outside with a delicious aioli dip.
Good beer selection and super nice bartender! Highly recommend.
Great old fashion
Great place. Upscale cocktail bar in Brooklyn. I think it's a good place to start your night or even stay there and have a few drinks with friends for the rest of the night.
(Translated by Google) Top cocktails!  (Original) Top cocktails !
Far and away the best bar in Bushwick. Fantastic atmosphere, great service, and incredible food and cocktails. Can't recommend strongly enough.

Highly recommend The Topaz - Great food, equally great drinks served in a very cool space.  Brandon, the owner, was very personable and grabbed my friend and I free shots to cheer someone on their birthday. It feels kind of speak-easy/art deco inside without a touch of pretention that you'd find in other similar bars.  Nice small backyard area, as well as another room with a piano in the back.  Great spot to bring a date.

Really loved this place. The drinks were great, the prices were reasonable and the service was fantastic. Even when we had a small issue with the order, the owner made it a point to make up for it and truly made sure we were taken care of. This place is a GEM!
Cool vibe and good drinks
Food and drinks were amazing.
(Translated by Google) Nice and with a good atmosphere  (Original) Bonito y con buen ambiente
Great atmosphere and a really creative drinks menu. Perfect for a date or gathering of friends.

The bartenders/servers are friendly, greeted us right when we walked in, great hospitality!  The Topaz offers a variety of drinks, the classics and new mixes. Their menu is tapas style, which is a step up from normal bar food. However, there is no correlation between the items. Some may find that weird but I think the diversity is great!  The Topaz is definitely worth checking out!
Fanciest spot around but..........better bars around with better vibes.

Loved the atmosphere of this place, it's located right off of the Montrose stop on the L line. This bar is spacious yet very intimate, definitely a great spot to bring your hot date. I liked the decor and high ceilings. Didn't get a chance to sit at the marble bar but the tables were comfy.  The bartenders/servers are friendly, greeted us right when we walked in, great hospitality!  The Topaz offers a variety of drinks, the classics and new mixes. Their menu is tapas style, which is a step up from normal bar food. However, there is no correlation between the items. Some may find that weird but I think the diversity is great!  The Topaz is definitely worth checking out!
Love this place.   It's the only place I hang out!

Brandon was extremely accommodating for my fiancee's surprise birthday party. The drinks were great. The back room I rented out was perfect. The staff was very friendly. Would love to do another private party there, soon.
Good cocktails. Great snacks. Big backroom. Small patio. Grilled cheese is stand out.

I came here on a Sunday night for a friend's birthday rendezvous. It's really a "diamond in the rough" in the neighborhood. I legit walked past it...very unassuming. The bartenders are pretty chill. I love the whole set up of this place...HGTV Haven complete with marble bar and hand carved seats? They even have a backroom space where they accommodate larger parties which is complete with sound system and a piano. ANDDDD they have a backyard. I'm really excited to see what this place looks like in the summertime. The food is all THAT and the bartenders know what they are doing when it comes to drinks. I had one of the best grilled cheese sandwiches in my life at this place..

Easily some of the best cocktails I've ever had. Great skilled bartenders. An amazing Old Fashioned with great presentation also happens to be a happy hour special. Try 'The Dead Man's Mask'. Just awesome. I really like this place.
Excellent cocktails, great bartenders.
Good cocktails and great food!  Date spot.
Great atmosphere, delicious food, and the drinks are decent.  Try their Moscow mule!

A beautiful surprise! Knowledgable, and friendly staff that know their craft. It's nothing fancy, but definitely a brilliant place for cocktails (can't say that about food because we didn't have any). The locale is a bit different compared to other fancy places, but The Topaz is in itself in a neighborhood that is a nook (Bushwick) in the great borough that is Brooklyn--definitely an up and coming neighborhood and The Topaz is a great addition! The ambience is delicate, yet refreshing--it is equipped with well appointed washrooms (again, simple and delicate). Overall theme is ab-fab! Worth a few visits (if you can get here--cars are easiest, public transpo might be tough).
Owners put a lot of thought and skill into putting together a great decor mixing new and rustic elements. Check out the new back patio!

unparalleled aesthetic - this is what an upstanding watering hole should strive to be.  If you want a dive bar, go somewhere else.  If you want craftsmanship and atmosphere, go to the Topaz.  While you're there, don't forget to look around. The interior fixtures and design are a world class work of art.

If you're looking for a low key place to have libations with a great crowd, The Topaz is your spot. Bartenders are on point to guide you through the night with delicious cocktails and amazing food. Seriously, try the Bao Buns.  Definite gem in East Williamsburg/ Bushwick. Conveniently located 1 block south from the Montrose L stop.
Beautiful and classy ambience.  The interior was beautifully crafted with marble tables and beautiful lights, etc. great cocktails and pork buns.
Beautiful bar with a great atmosphere! Go for the old-fashioneds, stay for the dance parties.

Was looking for a spot easily accessible off the L and this place was perfect. Brilliant cocktail list and a stellar beer selection. Had some of the food as well - one of the best grilled cheeses I've had in a long time, complemented by some Japanese steamed buns.  The space itself is great, with the decor of it all adding to the Topaz's charm. It's pretty big, especially for a Williamsburg/Bushwick bar, but maintains a comfortable and welcoming vibe. There's your more formal bar area at the front, then a big room at the back (which, after reading earlier comments, I believe you can rent out for parties etc). But what's got me looking forward to summer is the outdoor/garden area they have!  I'll definitely be back, even before winter is out.

If I were a single gentleman, this would be my go-to first date bar. The vibe in this establishment is what all bars should strive for- Great Drinks, Great Music, Great Service, Great Space Layout. Have been numerous times with friends and have always had a fun night. Also, the food is fantastic with a great Asian flavor.  Can even host a private event in the backroom and a nice backyard area for the summer. A distinct bar that is both classy and hip.
Spacious. Creative cocktails. Great for groups.

These guys are really doing it right. Having built a beautiful place by hand they are now crafting five star cocktails, with a slowly School, or the Pale Horse and get some pork buns for your belly.  Nothing else like it in the neighbourhood!
Amazing craft cocktails, delicious Japanese influenced tapas, and a beautiful decor. A++ DATE SPOT. They also have a big back room you can book for private parties without paying extra.

Great classy cocktail bar right by Montrose L stop. Cocktails are very interesting and slightly cheaper than pretty much anything you'll get in Williamsburg or  Manhattan. Good selection of cheap beers and some good small plates as well.
really great cocktails. the bartenders were friendly and the space is nice. definitely worth checking out.

Cool new bar that I finally stopped in after walking by a few times. Super close to the L train (Montrose stop).  Really liked the vibe and it was nice that they had a small patio in the back.  Surprised they had a small kitchen that mad really good pork buns.  Good cocktails.
